Philippine Stocks: ISM Communications, Manila Jockey, MRC

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-05-26T04:47:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-26/philippine-equity-movers-ism-communications-manila-jockey.html
Shares of the following companies had
unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the noon close in  Manila .  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index rose 0.9 percent to
4,230.56, gaining for the first time in six days.  ISM Communications Corp. (ISM)   jumped 6.5 percent to
3.11 pesos, the sharpest gain since Jan. 14. The company may
invest in a new business with the proceeds from the sale of a
stake in a telephone company, the Philippine Star reported,
citing President Eric Recto. Recto couldn’t be reached in his
office for comment.  Manila Jockey Club Inc. (MJC)   plunged 8.4 percent to
1.74 pesos after the company said it will pay 5 centavos a share
in dividend, it’s smallest payout based on data going back to
2001.  MRC Allied Inc. (MRC)   gained 4.3 percent to 73 centavos,
the highest closing price since May 12. A total of 11.92 million
MRC Allied shares were traded today, the most since January. The
company will sign a $50 million private placement agreement with
a group of European investors next week and use the funds raised
to finance the exploration of its Tampakan-Kiblawan mine,
Philippine Star reported, citing President Benjamin Bitanga.
Bitanga couldn’t be reached in his office for comment.  To contact the reporter on this story:
